Eu amo o Brasil 🇧🇷💚

These past two years I have been connecting more with Brasilian friends and the Brasilian community around me. 
I was born in Brasilia Brasil and adopted at 2 days old by Irish American parents. My parents did their best to show me the culture with what they had available around them and of course I learned as much as i could as well.  Only recently as in the past two three years I’ve gotten to meet and connect with Brasilian friends. I was never around any other Brasilians in the states and other countries I lived in. So now I get to practice/learn my Portuguese, enjoy Brasilian food with friends regularly, samba and listen to Funk, pagode etc music with other Brasilians and that has brought me so much joy honestly. 
I chose Jen Brasil years ago as my artist name because of the pride I have for my home and roots and culture. I hope one day I can do some major things for Brasil but for now I have Brasil in my heart always.

Once I heard the mention of anxiety in this song it became a favorite on repeat‼️
I try to keep my page really positive but in all honesty I struggle with anxiety and had a really rough past two years. I closed a lot of circles and some were forcefully closed for me. I definitely learned a lot about my strength and perseverance. I took the time to deal with the things I was struggling with, and I did almost a year of emdr. I also made sure that I kept going to the gym as much as I could, I went to a Natropath to help with supplements naturally, I even had huge growth spiritually. 
Take everything one day at a time
Go or stay where you’re valued 
Give yourself grace 
Have a bad day or two but don’t let it take over because it’s easy to get sucked into that.
It can get lonely but at the end of the day you’re the only one that has to do the work to feel better and it’s always an ongoing thing. You have to work at it just like the gym etc. 
Love you all and I’m betting on you💚

Starting this year in peace and with positivity🕊️. I am not a resolution person, never have been. I always felt if you want to do something you don’t have to wait until January to do it. Granted things may take time but as long as you’re moving forward that’s what matters. If you make resolutions I hope you stick with them and I hope you are able to accomplish all you set out to do this year. Blessings to you all and your loved ones I hope we all have an amazing and life changing year✨🤍🙏🏽

I don’t know about yall but I’m actually really hard on myself. I stress myself out all the time with my thoughts 🤣🤣 I swear I don’t work hard enough in the gym, on songs on content etc.  Just cause you don’t see me post those things doesn’t mean I don’t think them, I just don’t post them because I really do try to be positive. That self narrative a lot of us have is not always nice, and we wouldn’t speak like that to a friend so why do we do it to ourselves🤷🏽‍♀️🤦🏽‍♀️
I spent the last year and change growing, healing, and completed over a year of therapy and it’s helped so much. 
This year I will make sure I’m putting the techniques I learned to use and really continue on being positive and focused. One thing about me is I’m persistent, i persevere and I don’t give up 🤣🤎
